cs.HC, cs.CYBER, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.HCI 

This paper focuses on the design and evaluation of interactions between healthcare providers and electronic health records (EHRs), which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of EHRs also involves issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). The paper discusses the presentation of clinical data for task-based planning, which could involve information retrieval (cs.IR) and information visualization (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates the usability and preference of the ClinicalVis system, which is a human-computer interaction topic (cs.HCI).
